## CSS Layout Rules — read before touching any stylesheet
When adding or debugging CSS in this project, always verify these:

### 1. HEIGHT INHERITANCE CHAIN
`height: 100%` resolves against the parent's *computed* height. If the parent
has `height: auto` (default), 100% resolves to `auto` — effectively no height.
- Trace every element from leaf to `<html>`: each ancestor must have an explicit
  height OR the leaf must use `100vh`/viewport units.
- This project uses `html,body{height:100%}` → `#app{height:100vh}` → flex
  children with `flex:1`. Preserve this chain.

### 2. FLEX OVERFLOW GOTCHA (min-height/min-width)
Flex children have implicit `min-height: auto` / `min-width: auto`, which
prevents them from shrinking below their content's intrinsic size.
- Any flex child that should scroll MUST have `min-height: 0` (or `min-width: 0`).
- Fixed-size siblings in the same flex need `flex-shrink: 0`.
- This project already does this on `#body-panels`, `#left-stack`, `#left-pane`,
  `#right-pane`, `.log`, `.frame-content`. Do not remove these.

### 3. SCROLL CONTAINER DIMENSIONS
`overflow-y: auto` only shows scrollbars when content overflows. Overflow
requires a constrained height — without one, the element just grows.
- Every `overflow-y: auto` must have a height constraint: either `flex: 1`
  inside a flex column (with `min-height: 0`), or an explicit height.
- An `overflow-y: auto` element with `height: auto` (default) will never scroll.

### 4. Z-INDEX REQUIRES NON-STATIC POSITION
`z-index` is ignored on elements with `position: static` (the default).
- Always verify the element has `position: relative | absolute | fixed | sticky`.

### 5. CSS-ONLY: NO !important WITHOUT A COMMENT
`!important` breaks the cascade and causes specificity wars. If you must use it
(there are a few legitimate cases), add a comment explaining why.

### 6. BORDER-BOX IS GLOBAL
`*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box }` is set. Padding is included
in width/height calculations. Don't add manual width corrections for padding.

### 7. DIAGNOSTIC CHECKLIST (before any CSS change)
- [ ] Can I trace the height chain from this element to `<html>`?
- [ ] If this is a flex child that scrolls, does it have `min-height: 0`?
- [ ] If this has `overflow-y: auto`, does it have a height constraint?
- [ ] If this has `z-index`, does it have a non-static `position`?
- [ ] Am I adding `!important`? If so, why not use higher specificity instead?
- [ ] Am I mixing `gap` and `margin` on the same flex container? Pick one.
- [ ] Have I checked the element's computed height/width in DevTools?